## Step 2: Calculate the probability of each genotype.
Since each parent has an equal chance of passing either allele, the probability of each genotype is as follows:
- $P(RR) = P(R \text{ from male}) \times P(R \text{ from female}) = 0.5 \times 0.5 = 0.25$
- $P(RW) = P(R \text{ from male}) \times P(W \text{ from female}) = 0.5 \times 0.5 = 0.25$
