For carbon-carbon double bonds, $k = 950 \mathrm{~N} / \mathrm{m}$ and $x_0 = 1.335 Å = 1.335 \times 10^{-10} \mathrm{~m}$. The energy required to stretch one double bond to $1.397 Å = 1.397 \times 10^{-10} \mathrm{~m}$ is $E_{\text{double}} = \frac{1}{2} \times 950 \times (1.397 \times 10^{-10} - 1.335 \times 10^{-10})^2$. We need to calculate this value.

