Total energy $= 3 \times E_{\text{single}} + 3 \times E_{\text{double}} = 3 \times (4.42225 \times 10^{-20}) + 3 \times (1.8259 \times 10^{-20}) = 13.26675 \times 10^{-20} + 5.4777 \times 10^{-20} = 18.74445 \times 10^{-20} \mathrm{~J}$.

## Step 8: Convert the total energy from Joules to $\mathrm{kcal} / \mathrm{mol}$.
